MyBroadband is hosting its 2018 CyberSec Conference on 22 August 2018 at The Venue in Melrose Arch. The MyBroadband CyberSec Conference is an exclusive technical conference, aimed at IT executives and IT professionals in South Africa. Hosted in partnership with Vodacom, the event will provide insight and tips from experts in the industry about the latest cybersecurity threats. The event will also promote discussions with industry leaders, provide a look at the state of email security, give insight into online threats and how to protect against them, and demonstrate a live hack. The MyBroadband CyberSec conference is made possible thanks to the support of South Africa’s top tech companies – Vodacom, Mimecast, Trend Micro, Galix, ContinuitySA, SensePost. 